==English==
===Etymology===
{ME}; Latin ''[[Centaurus]];'' ''Greek ''(Kentauros);'' (Eng. usg. ca. 14c)

===Noun===
'''Centaur'''

#{{greekmyth}}: one of a race of [[monster]]s having a head, trunk, and arms of a [[man]], and the body and legs of a [[horse]].
#{{astronomy}}: An icy [[planetoid]] that orbits the Sun between [[Jupiter]] and [[Neptune]].
#a skillfull [[horseman]] or horsewoman.
#(''Rocketry'') a U.S. upper [[stage]], with a restartable [[liquid-propellant]] engine, used with an [[Atlas]] or [[Titan]] booster to launch [[satellite]]s and [[probe]]s.

